"Number" property types are converted to javascript numbers before being passed to the underlying graphing engine. The definition objects declared by the engines accept the following settings:

|!Setting |!Description |
|>|[[settings allowed by all properties|Property Types]] |
|increment |Sets step value of the range slider. Should be positive. (default: `1`) |
|min |Sets the minimum allowed value in the range slider (default: `0`) |
|max |Sets the maximum allowed value in the range slider (default: `min + increment * 100`) |

The settings only affect how the number slider is configured in property configuration tables. min and max does not constrain values if users write in.
